The paper discusses the use of graph distances and proximity functions for detecting and classifying relationships among entities, which is a common topic in social network analysis and data mining. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of these techniques for fraud detection, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the analysis of properties of the distance metric, which is related to the field of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
